The paper presents a data-driven model trained on historical data to detect different types of accidents during the drilling process. This involves real-time signal processing and time-series comparison, which are common techniques used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The model is also designed to work in a real-time system, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of avoiding accidents, which is a concern in software engineering (cs.SE) and cybersecurity (cs.CR).
